WEBVTT

00:12.708 --> 00:14.057
Narrator:
AT THIS VERY MOMENT

00:14.101 --> 00:16.233
AT THE LONGBOROUGH SCHOOL
FOR BOYS,

00:16.277 --> 00:20.063
YOUNG NED HAD CONVINCED
EUGENE MULCHANDANI

00:20.107 --> 00:22.848
TO GO TO WAR.

00:22.892 --> 00:26.417
FOR NOT ONLY WAS IT PROOF
OF HIS UNDYING PATRIOTISM,

00:26.461 --> 00:31.422
IT WAS ALSO A MUCH-NEEDED ESCAPE
FROM AN ADVANCED GEOMETRY LESSON

00:31.466 --> 00:33.598
IN PROOFS
OF THE PYTHAGOREAN KIND.

00:33.642 --> 00:37.254
HOWEVER, LIKE ALL
ILL-ADVISED TROOP DEPLOYMENTS,

00:37.298 --> 00:39.648
IT DID NOT COME
WITHOUT ITS SHARE

00:39.691 --> 00:41.606
OF UNEXPECTED CASUALTIES.

00:48.178 --> 00:51.094
AS THEY APPROACHED
THEIR FIRST COMBAT FATALITY,

00:51.138 --> 00:54.793
EUGENE'S EMOTIONAL RADAR
WAS OVERCOME,

00:54.837 --> 00:58.580
FORCING A HASTY RETREAT.

00:58.623 --> 01:02.323
YOUNG NED, ON THE OTHER HAND,
STOOD HIS GROUND.

01:02.366 --> 01:06.501
HE RATIONALIZED THAT IF HE
SOLVED THE HUNTER'S MURDER,

01:06.544 --> 01:13.073
THE ACCLAIM WOULD BRING
HIS FATHER BACK INTO HIS LIFE.

01:13.116 --> 01:15.162
BUT THE HUNTER REVEALED
HIS CAUSE OF DEATH

01:15.205 --> 01:17.947
WAS ACCIDENTAL
AND SELF-INFLICTED.

01:17.990 --> 01:21.211
THERE WAS NO MURDERER
TO BE CAUGHT.

01:21.255 --> 01:24.171
THOUGH THE PARK RANGER
WOULD BELIEVE OTHERWISE.

01:24.214 --> 01:28.175
WAKING THE DEAD
HAD LANDED YOUNG NED IN JAIL.

01:28.218 --> 01:29.654
BOTH BOYS WERE PERCEIVED,

01:29.698 --> 01:32.222
BY PAPEN COUNTY JUVENILE
CORRECTION OFFICERS,

01:32.266 --> 01:34.572
AS ANYTHING BUT HEROES.

01:37.271 --> 01:41.144
AND WHILE HIS COMRADE SECURED
AN HONORABLE DISCHARGE

01:41.188 --> 01:46.193
THROUGH THE STRENGTH
OF HIS PARENTAL ALLIES...

01:46.236 --> 01:48.978
...YOUNG NED REALIZED
THAT HIS FATHER

01:49.021 --> 01:52.242
WAS NOT GOING TO FIGHT
HIS BATTLES FOR HIM.

01:52.286 --> 01:53.809
FOR IN JAIL, AS IN LIFE,

01:53.852 --> 01:57.160
HE NEEDED TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR HIS ACTIONS.

01:57.204 --> 01:58.640
Chuck: DAD!

01:58.683 --> 02:00.946
IT'S 20 YEARS, 10 MONTHS,
8 DAYS, 4 HOURS

02:00.990 --> 02:02.600
AND 17 MINUTES LATER.

02:02.644 --> 02:06.691
ONCE AGAIN, WAKING THE DEAD
WAS A CAUSE FOR CONCERN.

02:06.735 --> 02:10.042
THE DEAD IN THIS INSTANCE
WAS CHUCK'S FATHER,

02:10.086 --> 02:13.002
CHARLES CHARLES,
WHO HAD CHOSEN TO FLEE.

02:18.616 --> 02:21.228
Ned: WHAT'S HE DOING?
WHERE'S HE GOING?

02:21.271 --> 02:23.665
THAT'S MY CAR.
HE STOLE MY CAR!

02:23.708 --> 02:26.407
HE'S NOT SUPPOSED TO LEAVE.
HE'S MY DAD.

02:26.450 --> 02:28.060
THIS IS REALLY BAD.

02:28.104 --> 02:29.627
THIS...

02:29.671 --> 02:30.933
IS REALLY...

02:30.976 --> 02:32.369
BAD.

02:32.413 --> 02:35.938
REALLY, REALLY, REALLY,
REALLY, REALLY BAD.

02:35.981 --> 02:39.289
HE JUST LEFT --
NO EXPLANATION, NO APOLOGY,

02:39.333 --> 02:40.725
NO FORWARDING ADDRESS.

02:40.769 --> 02:42.510
AT LEAST MY DAD LEFT
A FORWARDING ADDRESS

02:42.553 --> 02:44.120
TO A NEW HOUSE,
COMPLETE WITH A NEW FAMILY.

02:44.164 --> 02:45.600
NOW I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

02:45.643 --> 02:47.950
LOSING YOUR DAD BECAUSE HE DIES
IS HORRIBLE ENOUGH,

02:47.993 --> 02:49.995
BUT LOSING HIM
BECAUSE HE CHOOSES TO LEAVE

02:50.039 --> 02:52.128
IS JUST REALLY HORRIBLE.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.348
BASICALLY I'VE BEEN DUMPED
BY MY OWN DAD.

02:54.391 --> 02:56.045
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
DAD-DUMPED.

02:56.088 --> 02:57.699
I'M THE ONE HE'S MAD AT.

02:57.742 --> 03:00.789
HE ASKED YOU TO CHOOSE --
ME OR HIM. IT'S MY FAULT.

03:00.832 --> 03:02.051
I'M THE REASON HE LEFT
AFTER YOU RISKED

03:02.094 --> 03:03.531
EVERYTHING
TO BRING HIM BACK.

03:03.574 --> 03:06.229
I RISKED YOU.
I USED YOU TO BRING HIM BACK.

03:06.273 --> 03:07.535
AND IT WAS WRONG
AND IT WAS SELFISH,

03:07.578 --> 03:09.232
AND WE'RE IN THIS MESS
BECAUSE OF ME.

03:09.276 --> 03:11.234
WHAT IF DAD GOES AND TELLS
PEOPLE THERE'S A PIE MAKER

03:11.278 --> 03:15.717
WHO HAS A KNACK FOR BAKING
AND...WAKING DEAD PEOPLE?

03:15.760 --> 03:16.892
CHANGE OF CAREER?

03:16.935 --> 03:19.286
NO MORE WAKING
AND/OR BAKING.

03:19.329 --> 03:22.245
I JUST WANT TO
HOLD YOUR HAND.

03:22.289 --> 03:24.204
ME TOO.

03:35.084 --> 03:38.348
I AM DONE WITH THIS
BY-PROXY HAND JIVE.

03:38.392 --> 03:40.089
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?

03:40.132 --> 03:41.351
YOU TWO ARE ACTING
ALL LOVEY-DOVEY

03:41.395 --> 03:42.961
WHEN YOU OUGHT TO BE
SQUAWKING MAD.

03:43.005 --> 03:44.963
YOU SCREWED UP WHEN YOU USED
HIS WITCHIN' FINGER

03:45.007 --> 03:46.661
TO CONJURE UP A CORPSE
AND THEN NOT TELL HIM.

03:46.704 --> 03:50.012
YOU SCREWED UP BY NOT TAPPING
HER POPS WHEN YOU HAD THE CHANCE

03:50.055 --> 03:53.145
AND I SCREWED UP BY CAHOOTING
AND COLLUDING AND COVERING UP

03:53.189 --> 03:54.799
AND ENDED UP
HAVING ANOTHER DEAD BODY

03:54.843 --> 03:56.323
IN DEAR, OLD GHOST DAD'S
EMPTY GRAVE.

03:56.366 --> 03:58.368
AND BOTH OF YOU LADIES
OUGHT TO BE MAD AS HELL

03:58.412 --> 04:00.109
AT DEAR, OLD DEAD DAD
FOR STEALING YOUR CAR

04:00.152 --> 04:02.329
AND STEALING OFF INTO THE NIGHT
WITH A CORPSE FACE

04:02.372 --> 04:04.287
THAT AIN'T GONNA DO NO FAVORS
FOR NOBODY.

04:04.331 --> 04:05.897
NOW THAT YOU MENTION IT,
I AM MAD. I'M FURIOUS--

04:05.941 --> 04:07.856
OH, GET OVER IT, FOOL.

04:07.899 --> 04:09.727
BITCHIN' AND WHININ' TIME
HAS GOTTEN THE BOOT.

04:09.771 --> 04:10.989
WE NEED TO FIX THIS.
FIX WHAT, CHITCHATTERS?

04:11.033 --> 04:12.295
WHAT YOU FIXING?

04:12.339 --> 04:14.036
FIXIN' TO TELL YOU
TO MIND YOURS.

04:14.079 --> 04:16.125
ARE YOU WORKING A CASE?
WELL, BREAK IT DOWN.

04:16.168 --> 04:17.909
ARE THERE DEAD SOMEBODIES?
IS IT MURDER? MISSING PERSONS?

04:17.953 --> 04:19.302
WHO ARE THE PLAYERS?
LAY IT ON ME.

04:19.346 --> 04:21.217
THIS IS ONE OF THEM
NEED-TO-KNOW CASES.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.915
AND YOU DO NOT NEED,
THEREFORE YOU SHALL NOT KNOW.

04:23.959 --> 04:25.787
NO CASUAL CASE CHITCHAT

04:25.830 --> 04:27.919
TO PASS THE TIME
WHILST PERUSING THE MENU?

04:27.963 --> 04:29.747
WE DON'T CHITCHAT
WHERE WE EAT.

04:29.791 --> 04:32.359
BUT I'M YOUR ITTY-BITTY.
I'M HELPFUL.

04:32.402 --> 04:34.665
STRAWBERRY-KIWI CRUMBLE
A LA MODE.

04:34.709 --> 04:36.841
GOLDEN CHERRY CRIMSON PEAR,
ALSO A LA MODE.

04:36.885 --> 04:38.800
JUST COFFEE FOR ME,
THANKS.

04:41.672 --> 04:42.673
HOLD UP, YO.

04:42.717 --> 04:44.196
OH, BOY.

04:44.240 --> 04:45.937
I'M NOT SOME YO-YO
YOU CAN JERK UP AND DOWN

04:45.981 --> 04:48.462
ON A "TODAY LET'S INCLUDE HER,
TOMORROW LET'S NOT" WHIM.

04:48.505 --> 04:51.029
'CAUSE IF I AM,
THERE ARE ONLY SO MANY KNOTS

04:51.073 --> 04:54.163
I CAN TIE IN MY YO-YO STRING
BEFORE IT SNAPS...FOR GOOD.

04:54.206 --> 04:55.599
PLEASE, OLIVE.

04:55.643 --> 05:00.169
"PLEASE, OLIVE, " MY ASS.
WHERE'S MY PIE?

05:00.212 --> 05:02.954
Chuck: YOU KNOW WHAT? I HATE
THIS. OLIVE IS MY FRIEND.

05:02.998 --> 05:05.174
WE CAN'T MAKE HER OUR DEPOSITORY
OF SECRETS ONE MINUTE,

05:05.217 --> 05:06.697
AND THEN NOT INCLUDE HER
THE NEXT.

05:06.741 --> 05:08.612
WHY CAN'T WE JUST TELL HER
EVERYTHING?

05:08.656 --> 05:09.961
OH, LOOK AT THAT.

05:10.005 --> 05:12.224
A DUMB IDEA JUST FOUND A FRIEND.
THINK AGAIN.

05:12.268 --> 05:14.662
WE AIN'T GONNA POKE A STICK IN
OUR BUSINESS AND THEN

05:14.705 --> 05:17.099
SNAP IT OFF BY TELLING LITTLE
BIG MOUTH ALL OUR PROBLEMS.

05:17.142 --> 05:18.753
WELL, MAYBE LITTLE BIG MOUTH
HAS EARNED IT.

05:18.796 --> 05:21.059
ALL SHE DOES IS TRUST US
AND HELP US

05:21.103 --> 05:22.757
AND ALL WE DO IS LIE
TO HER.

05:22.800 --> 05:24.062
WE CAN'T AFFORD
TO TELL OLIVE.

05:24.106 --> 05:25.542
WITH EVERYTHING
THAT'S HAPPENING,

05:25.586 --> 05:27.675
WE DON'T NEED
ANOTHER UNFORTUNATE VARIABLE.

05:27.718 --> 05:29.981
[ GRUMBLES ]

05:30.025 --> 05:31.679
Narrator:
LITTLE DID THEY KNOW,

05:31.722 --> 05:34.638
ANOTHER UNFORTUNATE VARIABLE
WAS ALREADY ON ITS WAY...

05:34.682 --> 05:36.205
IN THE FORM OF ONE HALF

05:36.248 --> 05:38.642
OF A RENOWNED
SYNCHRONIZED-SWIMMING DUO

05:38.686 --> 05:40.557
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
AND SISTER NEUROTICS,

05:40.601 --> 05:41.863
WHO WAS CALLED...

05:41.906 --> 05:43.343
MISS VIVIAN!

05:43.386 --> 05:45.954
WELL, UH, TO WHAT DO I OWE
THE PLEASURE?

05:45.997 --> 05:48.696
I NEED YOU TO FIND SOMEONE
FOR ME --

05:48.739 --> 05:50.915
DWIGHT DIXON,
MY GENTLEMAN CALLER.

05:50.959 --> 05:55.137
HE HASN'T COME CALLING SINCE
OUR LAST RENDEZVOUS WENT AWRY.

05:55.180 --> 05:57.966
SOMETHING HORRIBLE
HAS HAPPENED!

05:58.009 --> 06:00.403
Narrator: THE FACTS,
AS EMERSON COD KNEW THEM

06:00.447 --> 06:02.405
AND VIVIAN DID NOT,
WERE THESE --

06:02.449 --> 06:06.235
DWIGHT DIXON ROMANCED VIVIAN
TO GET WHAT HE WANTED,

06:06.278 --> 06:08.411
AND WHAT HE WANTED
WAS A WATCH.

06:08.455 --> 06:11.632
I HAVE A SMALL CONFESSION
ABOUT CHARLES'S POCKET WATCH.

06:11.675 --> 06:13.198
WE BURIED IT
WITH OUR NIECE,

06:13.242 --> 06:14.765
LONELY TOURIST
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

06:14.809 --> 06:16.550
Narrator: DWIGHT DUG UP
HER NIECE'S GRAVE,

06:16.593 --> 06:19.988
BUT FOUND THE WATCH MISSING
AND CHUCK STILL ALIVE.

06:20.031 --> 06:21.424
VERY NICE
TO MEET YOU.

06:21.468 --> 06:23.644
SO DWIGHT DIXON
STOLE THE WATCH FROM CHUCK

06:23.687 --> 06:26.168
AND LILY STOLE THE WATCH
FROM DWIGHT,

06:26.211 --> 06:28.736
BUT SHE DIDN'T STOP
WITH ONE WATCH,

06:28.779 --> 06:30.694
SHE STOLE
DWIGHT'S WATCH, TOO.

06:30.738 --> 06:33.436
BELIEVING CHUCK AND THE
PIE MAKER TO BE THE THIEVES,

06:33.480 --> 06:36.613
DWIGHT DIXON SET ABOUT
TO KILL THEM BOTH,

06:36.657 --> 06:38.485
BUT DWIGHT FAILED TO REALIZE

06:38.528 --> 06:42.184
HIS MURDEROUS PLAN MADE HIM
THE TARGET OF A COSMIC EXCHANGE

06:42.227 --> 06:45.056
THAT ALLOWED CHUCK
TO KEEP HER FATHER ALIVE.

06:45.100 --> 06:48.625
WHILE TAKING
DWIGHT'S LIFE IN TRADE --

06:48.669 --> 06:51.019
AN ACCIDENTAL, INADVERTENT DEATH

06:51.062 --> 06:55.066
THAT EMERSON COD HID
IN ORDER TO PROTECT HIS FRIENDS.

06:55.110 --> 06:58.330
AND SO DWIGHT DIXON,
VILLAIN AND THIEF,

06:58.374 --> 06:59.941
WAS BURIED IN THE GRAVE

06:59.984 --> 07:02.726
ONCE OCCUPIED
BY CHARLES CHARLES.

07:04.293 --> 07:05.686
UH, W-WHAT MAKES YOU THINK

07:05.729 --> 07:07.339
SOMETHING HAPPENED
TO DWIGHT DIXON?

07:07.383 --> 07:08.776
BECAUSE
HE CARED ABOUT ME.

07:08.819 --> 07:10.908
HE WOULDN'T JUST LEAVE
WITHOUT EXPLANATION.

07:10.952 --> 07:12.954
EVEN WORSE,
HE COULD BE DEAD.

07:12.997 --> 07:15.609
WELL, LET'S NOT
JUMP TO CONCLUSIONS.

07:15.652 --> 07:17.959
LET'S JUST START
WITH THE FACTS, HMM?

07:18.002 --> 07:20.048
NOW, YOU SAY HE WAS
YOUR GENTLEMAN CALLER.

07:20.091 --> 07:21.223
HOW MANY TIMES
HE CALL ON YOU?

07:21.266 --> 07:22.529
THREE.

07:22.572 --> 07:24.269
HE CALL YOU
HIS GIRLFRIEND?

07:24.313 --> 07:25.532
GIVE YOU A SOCK DRAWER?

07:25.575 --> 07:27.185
OFFER YOU BLING?
NO!

07:27.229 --> 07:30.885
WELL, DID YOU TWO
HAVE, UH...intimate relations?

07:30.928 --> 07:32.582
VERY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:32.626 --> 07:34.976
LONG WALKS,
CLARINET CONCER--

07:35.019 --> 07:37.108
I MEANT
IN THE BIBLICAL SENSE.

07:37.152 --> 07:38.806
NO.

07:38.849 --> 07:40.590
WELL, THEN, ALLOW ME
TO PUT THIS TO YOU DELICATELY.

07:40.634 --> 07:42.505
YOU SEE, MEN ARE DOGS.

07:42.549 --> 07:44.507
THEY COME, YOU KNOW, SNIFFIN'
AROUND, BARKING UP YOUR TREE,

07:44.551 --> 07:46.988
BUT IF THEY DON'T SEE
A KITTY CAT UP IN THAT TREE,

07:47.031 --> 07:49.512
PRETTY SOON THEY JUST STOP
BARKING. DWIGHT AIN'T MISSING.

07:49.556 --> 07:51.862
HE'S BARKING UP
SOMEBODY ELSE'S TREE.

07:51.906 --> 07:54.386
DWIGHT WOULDN'T DO THAT.
HE'S A ROMANTIC...

07:54.430 --> 07:56.519
A ROMANTIC
WHO MAY NEED HELP.

07:56.563 --> 07:59.609
I'M ADVISING YOU TO NOT LOOK
FOR DWIGHT DIXON.

07:59.653 --> 08:02.830
THEN FIND HIM FOR ME
SO I DON'T HAVE TO.

08:02.873 --> 08:04.484
NOW, YOU LISTEN TO ME.

08:04.527 --> 08:06.050
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT KIND
OF MAN DWIGHT DIXON IS.

08:06.094 --> 08:07.704
HE'S A BAD MAN,
A SOCIOPATH,

08:07.748 --> 08:09.924
A MAN WHO'D JUST AS SOON
STAB A FRIEND IN THE NECK

08:09.967 --> 08:12.535
OR SHOOT 'EM IN THE BACK WITH A
LONG-RANGE, HIGH-POWERED RIFLE.

08:12.579 --> 08:14.885
DWIGHT DIXON'S GONE AWAY. NOW,
YOU JUST ACCEPT THAT

08:14.929 --> 08:17.279
AND STOP TRYING
TO BRING HIM BACK.

08:17.322 --> 08:20.325
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR TIME.

08:20.369 --> 08:22.327
Narrator: EMERSON COD
HATED DROPPING THE BOMB

08:22.371 --> 08:24.025
ON VIVIAN CHARLES'S HEART,

08:24.068 --> 08:25.896
BUT A SHOCK-AND-AWE CAMPAIGN

08:25.940 --> 08:29.900
WAS THE ONLY WAY
TO STOP HER SEARCH FOR DWIGHT.

08:29.944 --> 08:33.077
Emerson: SLICE ME UP
SOMETHING FRESH AND EXPENSIVE

08:33.121 --> 08:35.166
AND IT BETTER BE ON THE HOUSE,
'CAUSE I JUST SAVED

08:35.210 --> 08:36.907
BOTH OF YOUR
ASSES A WHOLE PILE OF GRIEF.

08:36.951 --> 08:38.213
WHY, WHAT HAPPENED?

08:38.256 --> 08:39.997
YOUR AUNT VIVIAN
CAME TO VISIT ME.

08:40.041 --> 08:44.001
SHE TRIED TO HIRE ME TO FIND HER
MISSING PARAMOUR, DWIGHT DIXON.

08:44.045 --> 08:45.699
WHAT DID YOU TELL HER?

08:45.742 --> 08:47.048
OH, I SAID,
"NO NEED TO PAY ME.

08:47.091 --> 08:48.702
"I KNOW DAMN WELL
WHERE DWIGHT DIXON IS --

08:48.745 --> 08:50.573
BURIED IN THE GROUND
WHERE I PUT HIM."

08:50.617 --> 08:52.183
WHAT YOU THINK I SAID?
I SAID NO.

08:52.227 --> 08:53.533
POOR VIVIAN.
SHE'S CARRYING A TORCH

08:53.576 --> 08:54.838
FOR A FLAME I EXTINGUISHED.

08:54.882 --> 08:57.145
-WITH MY FINGER.
-WELL, DON'T WORRY.

08:57.188 --> 08:59.060
I GAVE HER PLENTY OF REASONS
TO FORGET ALL ABOUT HIM.

08:59.103 --> 09:01.192
THE LAST THING WE NEED
IS SOMEBODY INVESTIGATING

09:01.236 --> 09:02.846
THE DISAPPEARANCE
OF DWIGHT DIXON.

09:02.890 --> 09:04.761
[ BELL RINGS ]

09:04.805 --> 09:08.678
Magnus: [ Norwegian accent ]
GOOD DAY, EMERSON COD. HIDE.

09:12.029 --> 09:14.031
[ Disdainfully ]
HELLO, MAGNUS.

09:14.075 --> 09:16.730
WE'VE BEEN CONSIGNED
TO INVESTIGATE

09:16.773 --> 09:18.470
THE DISAPPEARANCE
OF DWIGHT DIXON.

09:24.172 --> 09:25.826
Emerson: [ Disdainfully ]
HELLO, MAGNUS.

09:25.869 --> 09:27.392
IF IT ISN'T PAPEN COUNTY'S

09:27.436 --> 09:29.830
MOST SURPRISINGLY SUCCESSFUL
PRIVATE DETECTIVE.

09:29.873 --> 09:33.355
[ Norwegian accent ]
AND HIS PIE-BAKING,
PRETTY-BOY SIDEKICK.

09:33.398 --> 09:35.749
AS FLATTERING AS THAT IS,
YOU'RE NOT WELCOME HERE.

09:35.792 --> 09:38.708
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]
YOU EITHER, HEDDA.
STAY OUT OF MY KITCHEN.

09:42.538 --> 09:45.497
I'M STILL MAD, IGNORE MY CARING
TONE, BUT WHY ARE WE HIDING?

09:45.541 --> 09:48.544
Narrator:
CHUCK WAS HIDING TO AVOID
A CRACK FORENSIC TEAM

09:48.588 --> 09:51.982
FROM DISCOVERING
SHE WAS INFAMOUS MURDER VICTIM

09:52.026 --> 09:54.594
LONELY TOURIST
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

09:54.637 --> 09:57.684
AS PROUD MEMBERS
OF THE NORWEGIAN MINISTRY

09:57.727 --> 09:59.511
OF JUSTICE AND POLICE,

09:59.555 --> 10:02.123
LEAD DETECTIVE
MAGNUS OLSDATTER,

10:02.166 --> 10:05.126
HIS TRUSTED CRIMINALIST,
NILS NILSEN,

10:05.169 --> 10:07.998
AND LOYAL PROFILER
HEDDA LILLIHAMMER,

10:08.042 --> 10:11.872
WERE AN INVESTIGATIVE TRIO
WITHOUT EQUAL

10:11.915 --> 10:13.656
UNTIL THEIR BELOVED HOMELAND,

10:13.700 --> 10:18.487
RANKED AN ASTONISHING 37th
IN THE WORLD OF HOMICIDES,

10:18.530 --> 10:21.577
NO LONGER DEEMED
THEIR SERVICES NECESSARY.

10:21.621 --> 10:23.753
THEY ABANDONED THEIR MOTHERLAND

10:23.797 --> 10:27.191
WHEN REPORTS OF A SMALL PLACE
WITH A BIG MURDER RATE

10:27.235 --> 10:30.325
HALFWAY AROUND THE WORLD
CAUGHT THEIR EYE --

10:30.368 --> 10:33.371
POSITIVE THEIR FORENSIC KNOW-HOW
AND ADVANCED SKILL SET

10:33.415 --> 10:37.854
WOULD MAKE THEM A BIG FISH
IN A SMALL BUT LUCRATIVE POND,

10:37.898 --> 10:41.641
ONLY TO FIND THEMSELVES
CONSISTENTLY TRUMPED

10:41.684 --> 10:44.208
BY A LARGE FISH OF ANOTHER KIND

10:44.252 --> 10:47.734
BY THE NAME OF COD...
EMERSON COD.

10:47.777 --> 10:50.040
TODAY OUR SERVICES WERE
COMMISSIONED BY VIVIAN CHARLES

10:50.084 --> 10:52.826
TO LOCATE A MAN
BY THE NAME OF DWIGHT DIXON.

10:52.869 --> 10:54.175
IMAGINE OUR SURPRISE WHEN,

10:54.218 --> 10:55.959
DURING OUR DEBRIEFING
OF OUR CLIENT,

10:56.003 --> 10:58.005
WE BEGAN TO SUSPECT
THAT YOU KNEW SOMETHING

10:58.048 --> 11:00.311
ABOUT HIS DISAPPEARANCE
THAT YOU WERE NOT TELLING!

11:00.355 --> 11:04.141
[ Norwegian accent ]
TELL US NOW AND SAVE
YOURSELF THE HUMILIATION.

11:04.185 --> 11:07.057
I DON'T KNOW DIDDLY
OR SQUAT.

11:07.101 --> 11:09.973
UNFORTUNATELY FOR YOU,
THE FACTS SAY THE OPPOSITE.

11:10.017 --> 11:12.193
NILS, REFRESH
MR. COD'S MEMORY.

11:12.236 --> 11:16.066
FACT 1 -- VIVIAN CHARLES CLAIMS
YOU REFUSED HER CASE.

11:16.110 --> 11:19.548
HISTORY SHOWS EMERSON COD
NEVER TURNS DOWN EASY MONEY.

11:19.591 --> 11:21.681
HISTORY SHOWS
I HAD A FULL DOCKET,

11:21.724 --> 11:24.553
JUST LIKE MY POCKETBOOK.
IT WAS NOTHING PERSONAL.

11:24.596 --> 11:27.338
FACT 2 -- WHEN DISCUSSING DWIGHT
DIXON WITH MS. CHARLES,

11:27.382 --> 11:29.036
YOU REFERRED TO HIM
AS A...

11:29.079 --> 11:30.515
"BAD MAN, A SOCIOPATH,

11:30.559 --> 11:32.169
"THE KIND OF MAN
WHO'D STAB A FRIEND

11:32.213 --> 11:33.780
OR SHOOT HIM IN THE BACK."

11:33.823 --> 11:36.391
I WAS MERELY TRYING TO TALK HER
OUT OF A BAD RELATIONSHIP.

11:36.434 --> 11:39.002
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW THE MAN.
IT'S PURE CONJECTURE.

11:39.046 --> 11:41.309
FACT 3 --
IT WASN'T CONJECTURE.

11:41.352 --> 11:43.746
YOU AND DWIGHT HOBNOBBED
IN THE SAME CIRCLES!

11:43.790 --> 11:47.010
THE HELL I DID.
WE DIDN'T NOB NO HOBS.

11:47.054 --> 11:48.795
AND CERTAINLY NOT
IN NO DAMN CIRCLE.

11:48.838 --> 11:51.101
WE HAVE COPIES OF DIXON'S
CREDIT-CARD STATEMENTS --

11:51.145 --> 11:53.451
HE WAS A FREQUENT EATER
AT THIS VERY EATERY.

11:53.495 --> 11:55.932
THEREFORE, ESTABLISHING
A REASONABLE LINK, HMM?

11:55.976 --> 12:00.545
NOT REASONABLE -- UNREASONABLE
AND PURELY CIRCUMSTANTIAL.

12:00.589 --> 12:02.243
AND A LITTLE RUDE.
Magnus: NOT FOR LONG.

12:02.286 --> 12:04.854
FOR I BELIEVE WE WILL SOON PROVE
BEYOND A SHADOW OF A DOUBT

12:04.898 --> 12:07.248
THAT YOU'RE HIDING SOMETHING
OF IMPORTANCE TO THIS CASE.

12:07.291 --> 12:08.815
YEAH, HOW YOU PLAN
TO DO THAT?

12:08.858 --> 12:10.686
WITH HELP FROM OUR MOTHER,
THE MOST SOPHISTICATED

12:10.730 --> 12:13.950
MOBILE INVESTIGATIVE LABORATORY
FACILITY OF ITS KIND,

12:13.994 --> 12:16.387
PROVIDING INSTANTANEOUS
EVIDENCE COLLECTION,

12:16.431 --> 12:17.867
INSPECTION, AND DOCUMENTATION.

12:17.911 --> 12:20.348
IF THERE'S A SHRED OF EVIDENCE
CONNECTING YOU

12:20.391 --> 12:22.306
TO DWIGHT DIXON'S DISAPPEARANCE,
MOTHER WILL FIND IT.

12:22.350 --> 12:24.787
THEN RUN ON HOME TO YOUR MOTHER
BECAUSE YOU'RE NOT WELCOME HERE.

12:24.831 --> 12:29.096
THIS IS MY PIE HOLE. NO CLUES,
NO DIRT, NO SERVICE. NOW GO!

12:29.139 --> 12:31.402
YOU'LL FIND US
AT THE COME AND SLEEP HOTEL!

12:31.446 --> 12:34.014
BIG MOTHER IS WATCHING.
ANY LAST WORDS?

12:34.057 --> 12:35.145
UH...
HMM.

12:35.189 --> 12:37.017
THANK YOU.

12:37.060 --> 12:39.280
OW.

12:39.323 --> 12:41.108
[ SCOFFS ]

12:41.151 --> 12:42.457
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

12:42.500 --> 12:45.242
NOTHING.
NOTHING.NOTHING.

12:45.286 --> 12:46.983
WE ARE IN A CRISIS,
PEOPLE.

12:47.027 --> 12:49.856
WE NEED TO SHUT DOWN
THESE NORWEGIANS PRONTO-MUNDO.

12:49.899 --> 12:51.814
ALSO PRONTO-MUNDO,
WE NEED TO FIND MY DAD.

12:51.858 --> 12:54.295
PUT DADDY DEADBUCKS
ON HOLD.

12:54.338 --> 12:56.601
WE NEED TO CUT THESE NORSE FOOLS
OFF AT THE SOURCE.

12:56.645 --> 12:58.865
BUT WHAT IF THESE NORSE FOOLS
FIND CHUCK'S DAD?

12:58.908 --> 13:00.475
OR WORSE,
HE FINDS THEM AND TELLS THEM

13:00.518 --> 13:01.998
WHAT HAPPENED TO DWIGHT.

13:02.042 --> 13:03.826
AND THEN THERE'S
THE WAKING AND BAKING.

13:03.870 --> 13:05.872
IF HE WANTS ME
TO STAY OUT OF CHUCK'S LIFE,

13:05.915 --> 13:07.351
THAT'S ONE WAY TO DO IT.

13:07.395 --> 13:09.614
OKAY, FINE,
YOU LOOK FOR DADDY DEADBUCKS.

13:09.658 --> 13:11.965
BUT I STILL NEED SOMEBODY
TO TAKE A SECOND CRACK AT VIVIAN

13:12.008 --> 13:13.314
TO CALL OFF THE HOUNDS
WHILE I FIND OUT

13:13.357 --> 13:15.011
WHAT THESE NORWEGIANS DIG UP.

13:15.055 --> 13:16.404
I --

13:20.887 --> 13:23.019
OH, ITTY-BITTY.

13:23.063 --> 13:26.066
I'M ITTY-BITTY AGAIN?

13:26.109 --> 13:27.763
YOU MEAN IT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:33.160 --> 13:36.554
ALL I CAN TELL YOU IS
IF YOU DON'T CONVINCE VIVIAN

13:36.598 --> 13:39.253
TO CALL OFF HER INVESTIGATION
INTO DWIGHT'S DISAPPEARANCE,

13:39.296 --> 13:41.864
THEN WE ARE GONNA BE
IN A LOT OF TROUBLE.

13:41.908 --> 13:44.519
WHAT DID YOU DO,
KILL DWIGHT?

13:45.955 --> 13:48.653
I'M JUST KIDDING.
YOU DIDN'T, DID YOU?

13:48.697 --> 13:50.655
NO, BUT...
BUT WHAT?

13:50.699 --> 13:52.614
I STILL CAN'T TELL YOU
WHAT HAPPENED.

13:52.657 --> 13:55.878
OH, HELLS BELLS!
THE LEAST YOU COULD IS LIE.

13:55.922 --> 13:58.402
WHAT HURTS THE MOST
IS THE TOTAL LACK OF EFFORT.

13:58.446 --> 14:01.188
NONE OF YOU EVEN SEEM TO CARE
OR MIND THE FACT

14:01.231 --> 14:03.146
THAT YOU WON'T LET ME IN
ON YOUR SUPER-SECRET POWWOWS.

14:03.190 --> 14:04.844
I PROMISE YOU,
IT IS NOT OUT OF SPITE.

14:04.887 --> 14:06.193
WE'RE JUST TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU.

14:06.236 --> 14:07.847
BUT I DON'T NEED PROTECTION.

14:07.890 --> 14:09.022
THAT'S WHAT I HAVE SEVERAL

14:09.065 --> 14:11.154
LONG-STANDING
RESTRAINING ORDERS FOR.

14:11.198 --> 14:13.461
I NEED TO FEEL
LIKE I BELONG.

14:13.504 --> 14:15.767
I NEED TO FEEL
APPRECIATED, CHUCK.

14:15.811 --> 14:17.726
[ EXHALES HEAVILY ]

14:17.769 --> 14:19.597
I WANT
A FULL-FLEDGED MEMBERSHIP

14:19.641 --> 14:22.600
AND AN ALL-ACCESS PASS
TO THE P.I. PALOOZA.

14:22.644 --> 14:23.819
SO YOU'LL DO IT?

14:23.863 --> 14:24.907
YES.

14:24.951 --> 14:25.952
OH!

14:25.995 --> 14:27.388
THANK YOU,
THANK YOU.

14:27.431 --> 14:29.346
YOU'RE WELCOME.
YOU'RE WELCOME. YOU'RE WELCOME.

14:31.653 --> 14:35.483
Vivian:
I WILL NOT CALL THEM OFF,
NOT UNTIL THEY FIND DWIGHT.

14:35.526 --> 14:38.616
[ SCOFFS ] ARE YOU STILL
MOONING OVER THAT CREEP?

14:38.660 --> 14:39.922
MOONS WAX AND WANE.

14:39.966 --> 14:41.968
I AM STEADFAST
IN MY INVESTIGATION

14:42.011 --> 14:43.273
OF DWIGHT'S DISAPPEARANCE.

14:43.317 --> 14:45.014
I DON'T KNOW
IF VIVIAN'S TOLD YOU,

14:45.058 --> 14:47.712
BUT SHE'S HIRED A TEAM
OF NORWEGIAN P.I.s TO FIND HIM.

14:47.756 --> 14:49.584
RIGHT NOW, THEY'RE RUNNING A
COUPLE OF THOSE BRIGHT-BLUE

14:49.627 --> 14:51.455
BODY-FLUID LIGHTS
ALL OVER HIS MOTEL ROOM,

14:51.499 --> 14:53.109
LOOKING
FOR EVIDENCE OF FOUL PLAY.

14:53.153 --> 14:56.634
THERE'S BEEN FOUL PLAY?
S-SAYS WHO?

14:56.678 --> 14:58.201
AND WHO
ARE THESE NORWEGIANS?

14:58.245 --> 14:59.942
THEY CAME
HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.

14:59.986 --> 15:02.466
IN THEIR HOME COUNTRY, THEY'RE
THE MOST DECORATED FIGURES

15:02.510 --> 15:04.033
SINCE THOR BJORKLUND --

15:04.077 --> 15:06.775
INVENTOR OF THE HAND-HELD
CHEESE SLICER. OH!

15:06.818 --> 15:10.344
Narrator: LILY'S SUDDEN SPIKE
IN BODY TEMPERATURE STEMMED,

15:10.387 --> 15:12.346
NOT FROM HEARING
THOR BJORKLUND'S NAME,

15:12.389 --> 15:14.043
BUT FROM THE FEAR THAT

15:14.087 --> 15:16.524
IF DWIGHT DIXON
WAS THE VICTIM OF FOUL PLAY,

15:16.567 --> 15:20.049
AMONGST HIS POSSESSIONS,
THE NORWEGIANS WOULD DISCOVER

15:20.093 --> 15:23.531
A TRAIL OF EVIDENCE
LEADING THEM TO...

15:23.574 --> 15:24.967
LILY HERSELF.

15:25.011 --> 15:27.578
CALL OFF THE NORWEGIANS.
LET WELL ENOUGH ALONE.

15:27.622 --> 15:29.972
NOT UNTIL I FIND OUT
WHAT HAPPENED TO DWIGHT.

15:30.016 --> 15:31.365
NOTHING HAPPENED
TO DWIGHT!

15:31.408 --> 15:32.757
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

15:32.801 --> 15:34.629
WHAT I DO KNOW
IS DWIGHT WAS MENACING.

15:34.672 --> 15:37.414
HE EVEN SNUCK IN TO THE PIE HOLE
ONCE AFTER HOURS

15:37.458 --> 15:39.199
AND MENACED ME
RIGHT TO MY FACE.

15:39.242 --> 15:41.897
SEE? IT'S A GOOD THING
HE'S GONE.

15:41.941 --> 15:44.073
WHY ON EARTH
WOULD HE MENACE YOU?

15:44.117 --> 15:46.075
IT'S ON
A NEED-TO-KNOW BASIS.

15:46.119 --> 15:49.557
WELL, THEN,
I-I NEED TO KNOW.

15:49.600 --> 15:51.341
I'M TIRED
OF BEING A PUSHOVER.

15:51.385 --> 15:52.734
I DESERVE THE TRUTH,

15:52.777 --> 15:55.606
AND I DON'T NEED ANYONE
TO PROTECT ME FROM IT.

15:55.650 --> 15:57.086
YES, YOU DO.

15:57.130 --> 15:59.523
Both: WHY?

15:59.567 --> 16:01.482
I CAN'T TELL YOU.

16:03.005 --> 16:04.746
THIS GIVES ME PAUSE.

16:04.789 --> 16:06.400
A MANICURE MIGHT HELP.

16:06.443 --> 16:08.532
NO, PAUSE,
LIKE ONE STEP PAST "PLAY"

16:08.576 --> 16:10.273
AND NOT QUITE TO "STOP."

16:10.317 --> 16:14.147
BECAUSE I'VE BEEN HEARING THIS
CONVERSATION ON REPEAT ALL DAY,

16:14.190 --> 16:16.018
AND I'M FINALLY HEARING
THE MUSIC.

16:16.062 --> 16:17.846
AND I'VE HEARD ENOUGH TO KNOW
WHEN PEOPLE SAY,

16:17.889 --> 16:19.326
"I CAN'T TELL YOU.
IT'S FOR YOUR OWN GOOD,"

16:19.369 --> 16:20.849
WHAT THEY REALLY MEAN IS,
"I WON'T TELL YOU

16:20.892 --> 16:22.590
BECAUSE I DON'T TRUST YOU."

16:22.633 --> 16:24.374
BECAUSE THEY DON'T THINK
THAT YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE ENOUGH

16:24.418 --> 16:26.028
TO HEAR
OR HANDLE THE TRUTH.

16:26.072 --> 16:28.335
SO THEY HAVE THESE PRIVATE
CHITCHATS IN CORNERS

16:28.378 --> 16:30.293
AND IN BOOTHS. AND WHEN YOU
SHIMMY ON OVER

16:30.337 --> 16:32.469
TO JUST SAY A SIMPLE, "TOP O'
THE MORNIN' TO YA!"

16:32.513 --> 16:34.906
THEY CLAM UP AND AVOID YOU
LIKE YOU GOT THE EBOLA.

16:34.950 --> 16:37.039
AREN'T YOU TIRED OF FEELING

16:37.083 --> 16:40.303
LIKE YOU HAVE TO LIVE YOUR LIFE
FROM THE OUTSIDE?

16:40.347 --> 16:42.001
YOU DESERVE
TO HAVE THOSE ANSWERS.

16:42.044 --> 16:45.308
AND IF YOU WANT TO ENLIST
A CRACK TEAM OF P.I.s

16:45.352 --> 16:47.702
FROM THE LAND OF NORWEGIA,
YOU GO, GIRL!

16:47.745 --> 16:49.747
BECAUSE MAYBE THEN,
YOU'LL FINALLY GET

16:49.791 --> 16:51.314
THE RESPECT, TRUST,
AND HONESTY

16:51.358 --> 16:53.751
YOU DESERVE FROM YOUR
"SO-CALLED" BEST FRIENDS.

16:53.795 --> 16:56.624
Narrator: AS OLIVE SNOOK
BROKE RANKS WITH LILY

16:56.667 --> 16:58.843
AND CAME TO THE DEFENSE
OF VIVIAN,

16:58.887 --> 17:02.630
SHE BEGAN TO WONDER IF THERE
WERE OTHER ALLIANCES IN HER LIFE

17:02.673 --> 17:05.459
SHE SHOULD BE BREAKING.

17:05.502 --> 17:07.678
EMERSON COD
HOPED THAT ANY EVIDENCE

17:07.722 --> 17:11.900
THE NORWEGIANS GATHERED
FROM DWIGHT DIXON'S MOTEL ROOM

17:11.943 --> 17:13.858
WAS OF NO SIGNIFICANCE AT ALL.

17:24.826 --> 17:30.962
THAT'S LILY'S HANDWRITING.

17:31.006 --> 17:31.963
OH.

17:38.840 --> 17:39.841
HELLO, LILY.

17:39.884 --> 17:42.278
Lily: VIVIAN.

17:42.322 --> 17:45.977
LILY, I'M AFRAID THIS IS GOING
TO BE A CONFRONTATION.

17:46.021 --> 17:47.718
IS IT, NOW?

17:47.762 --> 17:51.592
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED AT THE CEMETERY

17:51.635 --> 17:53.724
BETWEEN YOU AND DWIGHT?

17:53.768 --> 17:59.078
NOTHING HAPPENED AT THE CEMETERY
'TWEEN ME AND DWIGHT.

17:59.121 --> 18:01.645
HE STOOD ME UP,
JUST LIKE HE DID YOU.

18:01.689 --> 18:03.386
I WASN'T STOOD UP.

18:03.430 --> 18:05.997
YOU RAN HIM OFF WITH BOTH
BARRELS COCKED AT HIS MANHOOD.

18:06.041 --> 18:07.956
THEN INVITED AND/OR LURED HIM
TO THE CEMETERY

18:07.999 --> 18:09.000
FOR HEAVEN KNOWS WHY.

18:09.044 --> 18:10.567
I WON'T CALL YOU A LIAR.

18:10.611 --> 18:13.179
IF YOU SAY HE DIDN'T SHOW,
THEN I BELIEVE YOU.

18:13.222 --> 18:14.658
HE DIDN'T SHOW.

18:14.702 --> 18:16.486
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

18:16.530 --> 18:18.009
I CAN'T PROTECT YOU
FROM THE NORWEGIANS

18:18.053 --> 18:19.576
IF YOU DON'T TELL ME
THE TRUTH.

18:19.620 --> 18:22.753
PROTECT ME? WHAT --
WHAT IS IT YOU THINK I DID?

18:22.797 --> 18:25.278
SOMETHING RASH.

18:25.321 --> 18:27.149
HONESTLY -- AND THIS IS
A PETTY ACCUSATION,

18:27.193 --> 18:28.716
THEREFORE I'M NOT PROUD --

18:28.759 --> 18:32.502
BUT I DON'T THINK YOU LIKE
THAT HE MADE ME HAPPY.

18:32.546 --> 18:34.678
DWIGHT DIXON IS TROUBLE.

18:34.722 --> 18:36.985
DWIGHT DIXON LAVISHED ME
WITH COURTLY BLANDISHMENTS

18:37.028 --> 18:39.683
AND PICNICS COMPLETE
WITH CRUDITES AND SOUP.

18:39.727 --> 18:41.511
THERE MAY HAVE BEEN
INVOLVEMENT

18:41.555 --> 18:43.774
WITH A CRIMINAL ELEMENT
IN HIS PAST,

18:43.818 --> 18:45.689
BUT THAT'S BEHIND HIM NOW.

18:45.733 --> 18:47.169
IT AIN'T BEHIND HIM.

18:47.213 --> 18:49.345
IT'S RIGHT ON TOP OF HIM,
IF NOT INSIDE HIM.

18:49.389 --> 18:52.218
HIS MOTEL ROOM
HAD ENOUGH BUCKSHOT

18:52.261 --> 18:54.176
TO BLOW COEUR d'COEURS
TO TIMBUKTU!

18:54.220 --> 18:57.136
WHAT WERE YOU DOING
IN HIS MOTEL ROOM?

18:59.050 --> 19:01.749
LOOKING FOR THIS.

19:01.792 --> 19:04.012
CHARLES'S POCKET WATCH.

19:04.055 --> 19:05.187
YOUR KIND DWIGHT

19:05.231 --> 19:07.885
STOLE IT
FROM CHARLOTTE'S GRAVE

19:07.929 --> 19:10.366
RIGHT AFTER YOU TOLD HIM
WHERE IT WAS.

19:10.410 --> 19:12.412
H-HE DIDN'T --
HE COULDN'T -- HE...

19:12.455 --> 19:14.979
HE DUG HER UP?

19:15.023 --> 19:18.113
HE DUG HER UP
AND TOOK IT FROM HER.

19:18.157 --> 19:20.724
SO I TOOK IT BACK
AND TOOK HIS WATCH, TOO.

19:20.768 --> 19:23.466
YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT WAS GONNA HAPPEN

19:23.510 --> 19:26.034
BETWEEN ME AND DWIGHT
AT THE CEMETERY IF HE SHOWED?

19:26.077 --> 19:28.384
ME AND BOTH BARRELS
WERE GONNA CONVINCE HIM

19:28.428 --> 19:30.952
TO DIG CHARLOTTE'S GRAVE
RIGHT UP AGAIN

19:30.995 --> 19:35.217
AND PUT THAT WATCH BACK
EXACTLY WHERE HE FOUND IT.

19:35.261 --> 19:39.003
AND YOUR INTENTIONS
AFTER THAT?

19:39.047 --> 19:41.310
THAT WAS GONNA BE
UP TO DWIGHT.

19:45.445 --> 19:47.142
CONGRATULATIONS, LILY.

19:47.186 --> 19:49.884
I KNOW HOW YOU LIKE
BEING RIGHT.

19:49.927 --> 19:51.320
I DIDN'T WANT TO BE RI--

19:51.364 --> 19:54.410
I KNEW I WAS GONNA BE,
BUT I DIDN'T WANT TO BE.

19:54.454 --> 19:58.458
I DON'T GET ANY SATISFACTION
FROM SEEING YOU HURT.

19:59.981 --> 20:02.897
NOW I REALLY
DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

20:05.291 --> 20:09.730
Narrator: AS THE COLD SNAP
BETWEEN THE AUNTS GREW COLDER,

20:09.773 --> 20:12.385
THE PIE MAKER AND CHUCK
WERE INVESTIGATING

20:12.428 --> 20:15.736
THE EQUALLY SERIOUS MATTER
OF THE MISSING CHARLES CHARLES.

20:15.779 --> 20:19.043
Ned: BRINGING BACK THE DEAD
IS ALWAYS COMPLICATED.

20:19.087 --> 20:20.436
SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO

20:20.480 --> 20:23.657
FOCUS ON THE TREE
INSTEAD OF THE FOREST.

20:23.700 --> 20:25.615
YOU HAVE TO FIND
THAT ONE THING

20:25.659 --> 20:30.664
AND THAT TINY GLIMMER OF HOPE
AND JUST HOLD ONTO IT.

20:30.707 --> 20:33.144
WAIT. WHAT'S THAT?

20:33.188 --> 20:35.973
IT'S ANOTHER BUTTON,
A BIG BRASS BUTTON.

20:36.017 --> 20:38.106
IT'S PLACED CONSPICUOUSLY
ON THE WINDOWSILL.

20:38.149 --> 20:40.282
IT MIGHT HAVE POPPED OFF
MY DAD'S SWEATER

20:40.326 --> 20:42.502
21 YEARS, 2 MONTHS,
AND 24 DAYS AGO --

20:42.545 --> 20:44.547
THE DAY HE MOVED OUT
AND ABANDONED ME.

20:44.591 --> 20:46.288
OR MAYBE IT'S A SIGN
FROM MY DAD.

20:46.332 --> 20:48.203
HE'D ALWAYS GIVE ME
A BUTTON TO HOLD ONTO

20:48.247 --> 20:49.944
ON LONG JOURNEYS
TO SUMMER CAMP,

20:49.987 --> 20:52.729
OR HE'D SNEAK ONE IN MY POCKET
ON THE FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL

20:52.773 --> 20:55.689
TO LET ME KNOW THAT HE WAS THERE
AND HE WAS WATCHING ME

20:55.732 --> 20:57.256
AND THAT EVERYTHING
WOULD BE OKAY.

20:57.299 --> 20:58.996
CHUCK, IT'S...

20:59.040 --> 21:02.348
MAYBE THE REASON THAT I CAN'T
BELIEVE THAT HE JUST LEFT

21:02.391 --> 21:04.393
IS BECAUSE HE DIDN'T.

21:04.437 --> 21:07.004
MAYBE HE'S KEEPING
A SAFE DISTANCE.

21:07.048 --> 21:08.658
IS THAT REALISTIC?

21:08.702 --> 21:12.358
MY LIFE HAS BEEN SO UNREAL.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT REALISTIC IS.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.621
I DIED...
AND THEN I WAS ALIVE AGAIN.

21:14.664 --> 21:16.536
AND SO WAS MY DAD,
AND IT'S SOMETHING

21:16.579 --> 21:20.235
THAT WE BOTH SHARE THAT NOBODY
ELSE CAN, WHICH IS WHY I KNOW.

21:20.279 --> 21:23.238
NED, I KNOW, AND I FEEL IT
DEEP, DEEP DOWN INSIDE OF ME

21:23.282 --> 21:25.240
THAT HE WOULDN'T
ABANDON ME.

21:25.284 --> 21:27.938
HE'S HERE.
HE'S HERE SOMEWHERE.

21:27.982 --> 21:29.113
UM...

21:29.157 --> 21:32.247
YOU CAN'T HANG ALL THAT
ON A BUTTON.

21:32.291 --> 21:33.640
YES, I CAN.

21:33.683 --> 21:35.685
I'M HIS BUTTON-BUTTON.

21:35.729 --> 21:38.297
Narrator: WHILE CHUCK HOPED
THE OLD, BRASS BUTTON

21:38.340 --> 21:42.910
WAS SIGNIFICANT EVIDENCE OF HER
FATHER'S COMFORTING PRESENCE,

21:42.953 --> 21:44.825
131 MILES DUE NORTH,

21:44.868 --> 21:48.176
THE NORWEGIANS CONTINUED
THEIR INVESTIGATION.

21:48.219 --> 21:51.527
ALL THE WHILE, KEEPING
A WATCHFUL EYE ON EMERSON COD,

21:51.571 --> 21:55.488
WHO THEY BELIEVED KNEW MORE
THAN HE WAS WILLING TO SAY.

21:55.531 --> 21:57.925
MEANWHILE,
EMERSON COD WAS ONCE AGAIN

21:57.968 --> 21:59.405
KEEPING HIS EYE ON THEM,

21:59.448 --> 22:02.190
IN THE HOPE
THAT THE FORENSIC BREAD CRUMBS

22:02.233 --> 22:03.670
FROM DWIGHT'S MOTEL ROOM

22:03.713 --> 22:06.934
WOULD NOT LEAD THE NORWEGIANS
BACK HIS WAY.

22:06.977 --> 22:10.329
USING THE GUMSHOE SKILLS
THAT MADE HIM GREAT,

22:10.372 --> 22:13.506
THE NUMBER-ONE DETECTIVE
IN PAPEN COUNTY

22:13.549 --> 22:15.421
TOOK THE FIGHT TO HIS OPPONENT.

22:15.464 --> 22:17.988
HIS PLAN WAS THIS --

22:18.032 --> 22:22.210
FIRST, ASSESS THE TRUE NATURE
OF THE THREAT.

22:22.253 --> 22:27.084
TWO, FIND AND EXPLOIT
THEIR WEAKNESSES, AND THREE...

22:27.128 --> 22:28.172
Olive:
SHUT YOUR MOUTH.

22:28.216 --> 22:29.739
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU GUYS THINK

22:29.783 --> 22:31.524
MY FORMER FRIENDS
ARE UP TO NO GOOD, TOO.

22:31.567 --> 22:34.353
Narrator: OH, HELL NO.

22:34.396 --> 22:37.486
DAMN YOU,
YOU ITTY-BITTY TRAITOR.

22:37.530 --> 22:39.096
I DON'T HAVE ENOUGH FINGERS
AND TOES

22:39.140 --> 22:41.403
TO COUNT THE SECRETS
THAT THEY FLAUNT IN MY FACE.

22:41.447 --> 22:43.144
OH,
AND THAT DWIGHT DIXON,

22:43.187 --> 22:45.494
HE DID HANG AROUND
THE PIE HOLE...A LOT.

22:45.538 --> 22:47.366
UNTIL HE DIDN'T.
AND THEN YOU GUYS SHOW UP,

22:47.409 --> 22:50.978
AND THEY'RE JUMPIER THAN A BUNCH
OF KANGAROOS ON A POGO STICK.

22:51.021 --> 22:53.894
SO, I COME
BEARING GIFTS.

22:53.937 --> 22:55.112
THE PIE MAKER'S
SALIVA --

22:55.156 --> 22:56.897
'CAUSE THEY HAVE THINGS
IN THEIR MOUTH

22:56.940 --> 22:59.682
AND IN THEIR HANDS THAT THEY
DO NOT WANT SPREAD AROUND.

22:59.726 --> 23:01.728
THE KINDS OF THINGS
THAT WOULD LEAD THEM

23:01.771 --> 23:03.120
TO KILL A MAN, PERHAPS?

23:03.164 --> 23:05.035
WELL, THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.
YOU TELL ME.

23:05.079 --> 23:06.646
THERE'S PLENTY OF
SOMETHIN'-SOMETHIN' GOING ON

23:06.689 --> 23:08.822
WITH THOSE DIRTY BIRDS, AND
SINCE YOU'RE ALL ABOUT

23:08.865 --> 23:10.780
GETTING ANSWERS,
AND SO AM I, I FIGURED

23:10.824 --> 23:13.217
IT WAS ABOUT TIME
I JOINED THE A-TEAM.

23:13.261 --> 23:16.395
WHICH IS WHY WE WERE EXCITED
TO RECEIVE YOUR INQUIRY

23:16.438 --> 23:18.309
ABOUT JOINING
OUR ORGANIZATION.

23:18.353 --> 23:22.313
Nils: THE DNA ANALYSIS
THAT I PERFORMED ON YOUR HAIR

23:22.357 --> 23:25.186
TOLD US EVERYTHING
WE NEEDED TO KNOW.

23:25.229 --> 23:27.144
OH. I WAS
UNDER THE IMPRESSION

23:27.188 --> 23:28.972
THAT PENICILLIN
WOULD CLEAR THAT UP.

23:29.016 --> 23:32.802
NO, WHAT HE MEANS IS
THAT YOU'RE OF GOOD, STRONG,

23:32.846 --> 23:34.587
SHAPELY NORWEGIAN STOCK.

23:34.630 --> 23:36.153
OH.

23:36.197 --> 23:37.981
SKAL!
SKAL! SKAL!

23:38.025 --> 23:39.374
SKAL.

23:41.942 --> 23:43.117
THANK YOU. THANK YOU!

23:43.160 --> 23:45.075
OH! YOU TOO.

23:45.119 --> 23:47.208
WHICH GOES WITHOUT SAYING
SINCE YOU'RE SO OBVIOUSLY

23:47.251 --> 23:48.688
FROM THE LAND OF NORWEGIA.

23:48.731 --> 23:50.690
AND, AS IT TURNS OUT, SO AM I,
SO IT MAKES IT

23:50.733 --> 23:52.213
SWELL TO BE HOME,

23:52.256 --> 23:54.302
[ Norwegian accent ]
DON'T YA KNOW.

23:54.345 --> 23:55.651
[ Normal voice ]
I MUST SAY,

23:55.695 --> 23:58.132
YOU GUYS HAVE SERIOUSLY
PIMPED THIS RIDE.

23:58.175 --> 24:00.482
THIS IS FANCIER
THAN LIBERACE'S CAMPER!

24:00.526 --> 24:02.223
MOTHER IS THE HEART AND SOUL
OF WHAT WE DO.

24:02.266 --> 24:04.617
WITHOUT HER,
WE'D BE JUST ANOTHER --

24:04.660 --> 24:06.749
EMERSON "CLOD"?

24:06.793 --> 24:08.490
[ LAUGHTER ]

24:08.534 --> 24:10.971
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK HAPPENED
TO DWIGHT DIXON?

24:11.014 --> 24:12.625
HE APPEARS
TO HAVE VANISHED.

24:12.668 --> 24:15.497
AND HOW HE VANISHED PROBABLY
WASN'T PRETTY LIKE YOU.

24:15.541 --> 24:17.456
HE HAD ENOUGH WEAPONS
IN HIS ROOM

24:17.499 --> 24:18.848
TO ARM
THE NORWEGIAN MILITIA.

24:18.892 --> 24:22.069
ALL EVIDENCE POINTS
TO A DANGEROUS MAN

24:22.112 --> 24:23.810
WITH A DESTRUCTIVE AGENDA

24:23.853 --> 24:27.030
WHO MOST LIKELY MET
WITH A VIOLENT END.

24:27.074 --> 24:30.338
ALL IN ALL, A BAD MAN.

24:30.381 --> 24:32.166
CAN YOU HANDLE MORE?

24:32.209 --> 24:33.907
IT'S GETTING HOTTER
FROM HERE.

24:33.950 --> 24:36.213
WE ALSO FIND A SHOVEL
UNDER DWIGHT'S BED.

24:36.257 --> 24:38.085
THE MINERAL CONTENT
OF THE CAKED-ON DIRT

24:38.128 --> 24:41.218
MATCHES THAT
OF THE LOCAL CEMETERY EXACTLY.

24:41.262 --> 24:43.351
MORE IMPORTANTLY,
WHAT DWIGHT DIXON WAS DOING

24:43.394 --> 24:46.310
BY CHARLES CHARLES'S
AND CHARLOTTE CHARLES'S GRAVES

24:46.354 --> 24:49.662
WITH THE SHOVEL,
WE CAN ONLY SPECULATE.

24:49.705 --> 24:51.315
FOR NOW.

24:51.359 --> 24:52.969
AN EXHUMATION ORDER.
[ GASPS ]

24:53.013 --> 24:56.233
YOU DON'T MEAN...
YOU'RE GONNA DIG THEM UP?

24:56.277 --> 24:57.539
JA.

24:57.583 --> 24:58.714
JA.

24:58.758 --> 24:59.802
JA.

24:59.846 --> 25:01.587
NO.
OLIVE'S A NORWEGIAN.

25:01.630 --> 25:03.589
MAYBE IT'S
STOCKHOLM SYNDROME.

25:03.632 --> 25:05.721
THEY'VE LURED HER IN, AND SHE
DOESN'T KNOW WHAT SHE'S DOING.

25:05.765 --> 25:08.507
CHITTY-CHATTY-BOO-HOO KNEW
EXACTLY WHAT SHE WAS DOING.

25:08.550 --> 25:10.944
SHE WAS SUFFICIENTLY LUBED
AND READY TO SPIT TACKS.

25:10.987 --> 25:12.728
SHE EVEN GAVE THEM
YOUR SALIVA SWAB

25:12.772 --> 25:14.077
TO GET
INTO THEIR CLUBHOUSE.

25:14.121 --> 25:15.905
WHAT WOULD THEY WANT
WITH MY SALIVA?

25:15.949 --> 25:17.559
IT'S MY FAULT. SHE WARNED US NOT

25:17.603 --> 25:19.169
TO PUSH HER,
AND THEN I PUSHED HER AWAY,

25:19.213 --> 25:20.910
AND I PUSHED HER
TO TALK TO VIVIAN,

25:20.954 --> 25:23.260
AND THAT PUSHED HER
TO SWITCH TEAMS.

25:23.304 --> 25:24.784
YOU'RE NOT THAT PUSHY,
AND YOU'RE NOT TO BLAME.

25:24.827 --> 25:26.786
OLIVE BETRAYED US
BECAUSE WE CAN'T LET HER IN,

25:26.829 --> 25:30.006
AND WE CAN'T LET HER IN
BECAUSE OF MY MAGIC FINGER.

25:30.050 --> 25:32.400
SOMEHOW OR OTHER, IT ALWAYS
COMES BACK TO MY MAGIC FINGER.

25:32.443 --> 25:35.403
MAYBE SO, BUT IN ABOUT FIVE
MINUTES, THE NORWEGIANS

25:35.446 --> 25:37.666
ARE GONNA HAVE THE COFFINS OF
DEAD GIRL AND HER POPS EXHUMED.

25:37.710 --> 25:40.843
AND WHEN THEY OPEN THEM UP,
THEY'RE GONNA FIND HERS EMPTY

25:40.887 --> 25:43.019
AND DWIGHT'S DEAD ASS
IN THE OTHER ONE

25:43.063 --> 25:45.848
AND ENOUGH FORENSIC EVIDENCE TO
LEAD THEM RIGHT BACK HERE TO US.

25:45.892 --> 25:48.677
Narrator:
STUNNED BY WHAT THEY HEARD, THE
PIE MAKER AND THE GIRL

25:48.721 --> 25:50.810
NAMED CHUCK PREPARED
FOR THE WORST,

25:50.853 --> 25:53.116
WHILE IN A GRAVEYARD
IN COEUR d'COEURS,

25:53.160 --> 25:56.555
THE NORWEGIANS
FOUND THEMSELVES UNPREPARED

25:56.598 --> 25:58.252
FOR THE SHOCKING DISCOVERY

25:58.295 --> 26:01.951
THAT EMERSON COD'S PREDICTION
WAS ONLY HALF RIGHT.

26:01.995 --> 26:04.040
BOTH COFFINS WERE EMPTY.

26:08.654 --> 26:10.307
Ned: EMPTY?
WHY ARE THEY EMPTY?

26:10.351 --> 26:11.657
I UNDERSTAND
WHY ONE OF THEM IS EMPTY.

26:11.700 --> 26:13.310
BUT WHY IS THE OTHER ONE EMPTY?
ARE YOU SURE?

26:13.354 --> 26:15.356
I MADE FRIENDLY
WITH THE GROUNDS KEEPER

26:15.399 --> 26:17.053
BY WAY OF A FEW BENJAMINS.

26:17.097 --> 26:18.751
THE NORWEGIANS POPPED
THE TOPS ON THEM COFFINS,

26:18.794 --> 26:20.317
SAW THEY WERE FULL
OF NOBODY,

26:20.361 --> 26:22.406
LOADED 'EM UP IN THE
MAMA-MOBILE, AND TOOK OFF.

26:22.450 --> 26:23.799
BUT HOW COULD MY DAD'S COFFIN
BE EMPTY?

26:23.843 --> 26:25.584
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE FULL
OF DWIGHT DIXON.

26:25.627 --> 26:27.281
OH, GOD.
WE BURIED HIM ALIVE.

26:27.324 --> 26:29.762
SHOULD I FEEL WORSE
Ã©\ABOUT YOU BURYING HIM ALIVE

26:29.805 --> 26:31.372
OR HIM GETTING OUT?

26:31.415 --> 26:32.721
AIN'T NOBODY BURIED ALIVE.

26:32.765 --> 26:34.810
DWIGHT DIXON IS DEADER
THAN A DOORNAIL.

26:34.854 --> 26:36.203
SOMEBODY MOVED THE BODY.

26:36.246 --> 26:38.640
WHO ELSE KNEW
HE WAS IN THAT COFFIN?

26:38.684 --> 26:40.468
MY DAD --
WHO ELSE COULD IT BE?

26:40.511 --> 26:41.687
"BUTTON-BUTTON" --
DON'T YOU SEE?

26:41.730 --> 26:43.514
HE MOVED THE BODY
TO PROTECT US.

26:43.558 --> 26:46.343
WHAT A GOOD DAD. YOU DON'T
SUPPOSE HE WIPED DOWN

26:46.387 --> 26:48.476
BOTH THE CASKETS WITH
INDUSTRIAL BLEACH, DO YOU?

26:48.519 --> 26:51.653
'CAUSE THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
THERE ISN'T GONNA BE SOME TRACE

26:51.697 --> 26:53.612
OF SOME FORENSIC TIDDLY-BIT
THAT'S GONNA LEAD EVERYBODY

26:53.655 --> 26:55.439
BACK TO EVERY SOMEBODY
AT THIS TABLE.

26:55.483 --> 26:56.702
THEY'RE GONNA FIND MY DNA,
AREN'T THEY?

26:56.745 --> 26:58.486
I SHOULD HAVE WORN
A HAIRNET.

26:58.529 --> 27:00.401
YOU CAN SAY THAT YOUR DNA
GOT THERE AT MY DAD'S FUNERAL,

27:00.444 --> 27:02.795
BUT, EMERSON,
YOUR DNA IS ALL OVER THE GRAVE.

27:02.838 --> 27:04.666
AND WITH NO REAL REASON
FOR IT TO BE THERE,

27:04.710 --> 27:06.799
YOU'RE GONNA LOOK GUILTY.
I AM GUILTY.

27:06.842 --> 27:09.192
IT WASN'T MY HAND
THAT TOUCHED CHARLES CHARLES

27:09.236 --> 27:10.803
AND PUT DWIGHT DIXON
IN THE GRAVE.

27:10.846 --> 27:12.456
AND IT DEFINITELY WASN'T
MY HAND

27:12.500 --> 27:15.111
THAT FORCED THE MAGIC FINGER
TO WAKE DEAR DEAD DAD.

27:15.155 --> 27:18.680
BUT NONE OF YOUR HANDS WOULD
BE DIRTY IF IT WASN'T FOR ME.

27:18.724 --> 27:22.989
HELL, YOU WERE JUST A PIE MAKER,
AND SHE WAS GRASS FERTILIZER.

27:23.032 --> 27:25.208
I BROUGHT YOU
INTO MY P.I. ORGANIZATION.

27:25.252 --> 27:28.298
IT WAS MY JOB TO KEEP YOU
IN LINE, AND I DIDN'T.

27:28.342 --> 27:31.693
SO IF ANYBODY DESERVES TO FACE
THE NORWEGIAN FIRING SQUAD...

27:31.737 --> 27:33.564
IT'S ME.

27:33.608 --> 27:36.393
DON'T PUT ON YOUR BLINDFOLD
OR SMOKE YOUR LAST STOGIE YET.

27:36.437 --> 27:37.786
I GOT A PLAN.

27:37.830 --> 27:39.135
YOU'RE GONNA TELL
THE NORWEGIANS

27:39.179 --> 27:40.615
EVERYTHING YOU KNOW.

27:40.659 --> 27:42.269
LET ME TELL YOU
EVERYTHING I KNOW.

27:42.312 --> 27:44.750
THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN TELL US
THAT MOTHER CAN'T

27:44.793 --> 27:46.316
ONCE SHE FINISHES
HER ANALYSIS.

27:46.360 --> 27:48.057
ALTHOUGH WE DON'T WISH

27:48.101 --> 27:50.625
TO LOOK A GIFT WHORE
IN THE MOUTH, MR. COD,

27:50.669 --> 27:52.932
WHY WOULD YOU TELL US
EVERYTHING YOU KNOW?

27:52.975 --> 27:55.717
WELL, CONFESSION
IS GOOD FOR THE SOUL.

27:55.761 --> 27:59.373
WHEN YOU LOOK AT A CASE
THROUGH A LENS OF A MICROSCOPE,

27:59.416 --> 28:03.029
YOU TEND TO REALLY MISS
ON WHAT MATTERS.

28:03.072 --> 28:04.726
IT'S THE PEOPLE,
PEOPLE --

28:04.770 --> 28:07.120
PEOPLE YOU WORK WITH,
CLIENTS YOU WORK FOR.

28:07.163 --> 28:08.687
CLIENTS
LIKE VIVIAN CHARLES?

28:08.730 --> 28:11.472
YOU CERTAINLY DIDN'T
PEOPLE-PEOPLE-PERSON HER.

28:11.515 --> 28:13.039
TRUE.

28:13.082 --> 28:15.824
WHEN YOU MAKE A MESS,
CLEAN IT UP!

28:15.868 --> 28:17.913
IT'S YOUR
RESPONSIBILITY.

28:17.957 --> 28:19.872
DETECTIVE WORK
IS A LOT LIKE MONEY.

28:19.915 --> 28:21.743
IT DON'T REALLY COME
WITH INSTRUCTIONS.

28:21.787 --> 28:25.051
I LEARNED THAT FROM THE GREATEST
DETECTIVE IN THE WORLD.

28:25.094 --> 28:27.444
OF COURSE, I'M TALKING ABOUT
SHAFT. YOU CAN DIG IT.

28:27.488 --> 28:30.970
Narrator: MEANWHILE,
AS EMERSON COD SERVED AS DECOY,

28:31.013 --> 28:33.581
ON THE STREET,
THE PIE MAKER AND CHUCK

28:33.624 --> 28:36.279
PREPARED TO ENTER
MOTHER'S EMPTY NEST.

28:36.323 --> 28:38.804
I LOVE "I HAVE A PLAN" NED.
WHO SAYS SPONTANEOUS IS SEXY?

28:38.847 --> 28:41.763
"SEXY" IS A MAN WITH
A TO-DO LIST, SOME SCHEMATICS,

28:41.807 --> 28:44.897
AND THE RIGHT TOOLS
TO HOT-WIRE A NORWEGIAN RV.

28:44.940 --> 28:46.812
SHALL WE?

28:46.855 --> 28:48.770
WE SHAN'T.
AT LEAST, YOU SHAN'T.

28:48.814 --> 28:50.076
I SHALL STEAL MOTHER
ALONE,

28:50.119 --> 28:51.947
AND YOU SHALL STAY HERE
AS A LOOKOUT.

28:51.991 --> 28:53.732
I SHAN'T DO
ANY SUCH THING.

28:53.775 --> 28:56.212
WE'RE IN THIS JAM BECAUSE
I BROUGHT MY DAD BACK.

28:56.256 --> 28:58.214
I DON'T BLAME YOU
FOR BRINGING BACK YOUR FATHER.

28:58.258 --> 28:59.868
I COULDN'T STOP MYSELF
FROM BRINGING BACK

28:59.912 --> 29:01.609
THE PERSON I LOVED EITHER.

29:01.652 --> 29:05.874
AND EMERSON NEVER FORCED ME OR
MY FINGER TO JOIN HIS P.I. TEAM.

29:05.918 --> 29:09.486
I POKED
OF MY OWN FREE WILL.

29:09.530 --> 29:12.098
AND SO IF THERE'S ANYONE
TO BLAME, IT'S ME.

29:12.141 --> 29:14.404
MY FINGER...

29:14.448 --> 29:16.102
MY FALLOUT.

29:16.145 --> 29:18.495
I'M DRIVING SOLO
THIS TIME.

29:32.161 --> 29:33.336
[ DOOR OPENS ]

29:33.380 --> 29:34.598
Both: YOU!

29:34.642 --> 29:36.426
THIS ISN'T
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

29:36.470 --> 29:37.993
YOU'RE NOT TRYING TO HOT-WIRE
MOTHER SO YOU CAN DRIVE AWAY

29:38.037 --> 29:39.995
WITH THE TRUCKLOAD OF EVIDENCE
THEY HAVE ON YOU?

29:40.039 --> 29:41.736
OKAY. IT IS WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.694
I'M SORRY
WE SHUT YOU OUT, OLIVE.

29:43.738 --> 29:46.262
THE LAST THING I EVER WANTED TO
DO WAS SHUT YOU OUT OF MY LIFE

29:46.306 --> 29:47.698
AND OPEN YOU UP
TO THE NORWEGIANS.

29:47.742 --> 29:50.005
IS THAT WHAT YOU THINK
THIS IS ALL ABOUT?

29:50.049 --> 29:51.398
-YOU GAVE THEM MY SWAB!
-PIG SPIT.

29:51.441 --> 29:53.313
DON'T DENY IT.
EMERSON SAW YOU.

29:53.356 --> 29:54.836
NO, DUMMY.
PIG SPIT.

29:54.880 --> 29:56.838
THE SWAB I GAVE THEM
CAME FROM PIGBY, NOT YOU.

29:56.882 --> 29:58.709
SO, YOU'RE NOT
A TURNCOAT?

29:58.753 --> 30:00.842
MORE OF A REVERSIBLE JACKET.
I WOULDN'T TURNCOAT ON YOU.

30:00.886 --> 30:02.713
I WAS WORKING DEEP COVER TO
DISMANTLE THIS OPERATION

30:02.757 --> 30:05.412
FROM THE INSIDE OUT.
I KNOW THEY HAVE DIRT ON YOU,

30:05.455 --> 30:07.893
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHAT THEY DID
TO MAKE YOU LOOK SO DIRTY.

30:07.936 --> 30:09.720
I GOT MYSELF DIRTY.

30:09.764 --> 30:11.853
WELL, ALLOW ME TO SOAP UP
THOSE HARD-TO-REACH PLACES.

30:11.897 --> 30:13.202
BY HELPING ME
DESTROY THE EVIDENCE?

30:13.246 --> 30:14.987
A SIMPLE "THANK YOU"
WOULD SUFFICE.

30:15.030 --> 30:16.815
OH, THANK YOU.

30:16.858 --> 30:18.642
THIS ITTY-BITTY'S ALWAYS ON
YOUR SIDE, NO QUESTIONS ASKED.

30:18.686 --> 30:20.514
WHAT IF I GUESSED?
OLIVE!

30:20.557 --> 30:23.386
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT DWIGHT
AND THOSE EMPTY COFFINS?

30:23.430 --> 30:25.084
I'M NOT
SUPPOSED TO TELL YOU.

30:25.127 --> 30:27.782
CAN YOU ANSWER YES OR NO IF
I ASK THE RIGHT QUESTIONS?

30:27.826 --> 30:29.523
CAN YOU ASK THE QUESTIONS
WHILE WE STEAL THE RV?

30:29.566 --> 30:32.221
THAT'S A YES-OR-NO QUESTION,
AND THE ANSWER IS YES.

30:32.265 --> 30:33.919
HO! OKAY.
GO!

30:33.962 --> 30:35.224
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

30:35.268 --> 30:37.183
POOR, HEARTBROKEN
VIVIAN CHARLES.

30:37.226 --> 30:40.490
WELL, I ADMIT I WAS INSENSITIVE
ABOUT THE SENSITIVITIES

30:40.534 --> 30:42.928
OF MS. VIVIAN
AND HER MISSING MR. GOODBAR.

30:42.971 --> 30:45.626
BUT I INTEND TO RIGHT THAT WRONG
COMING RIGHT UP.

30:45.669 --> 30:47.106
WOULD THIS BE
YOUR CONFESSION?

30:47.149 --> 30:48.977
THERE AIN'T GONNA BE
ANY CONFESSION.

30:49.021 --> 30:52.763
WE DON'T NEED YOUR CONFESSION
TO SOLVE THIS CASE --

30:52.807 --> 30:54.417
NOT WHEN WE HAVE MOTHER.

30:54.461 --> 30:56.158
[ MELODY PLAYS ]

30:56.202 --> 30:57.638
WHERE'S MOTHER GOING?

30:57.681 --> 31:01.424
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

31:01.468 --> 31:04.384
LOOKS LIKE YOU
ABOUT TO BECOME ORPHANS.

31:04.427 --> 31:05.472
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:05.515 --> 31:07.648
Hedda: STOP!
Nils: STOP!

31:07.691 --> 31:08.997
Magnus: STOP!
STOP!

31:09.041 --> 31:10.912
MOTHER!
MOTHER!

31:10.956 --> 31:13.349
MOTHER.
STOP.

31:13.393 --> 31:15.874
MOTHER.

31:15.917 --> 31:17.701
Olive: DO YOU KNOW WHY CHARLES
CHARLES'S GRAVE IS EMPTY?

31:17.745 --> 31:18.833
YES.

31:18.877 --> 31:20.052
WAS HIS GRAVE ROBBED?
NO.

31:20.095 --> 31:21.836
NO ONE TOOK THE BODY?
NO.

31:21.880 --> 31:23.577
THEN WHAT'D HE DO,
JUST GET UP AND WALK AWAY?

31:23.620 --> 31:24.708
YES.

31:24.752 --> 31:25.927
CHUCK'S FATHER'S ALIVE?

31:25.971 --> 31:28.321
YES. HOLD ON.

31:28.364 --> 31:30.845
[ TIRES SCREECH ]
AAH!

31:30.889 --> 31:33.239
WHEN CHUCK FAKED HER DEATH
AND HER FATHER FAKED HIS DEATH,

31:33.282 --> 31:34.588
WAS DWIGHT DIXON
ON TO THEM?

31:34.631 --> 31:36.242
YES.
OKAY. THEN HE DISAPPEARED.

31:36.285 --> 31:38.113
DID YOU HAVE ANYTHING TO DO
WITH HIS DISAPPEARANCE?

31:38.157 --> 31:39.723
YES. I DIDN'T MEAN TO,
BUT I DID.

31:39.767 --> 31:41.247
AND WHEN YOU INADVERTENTLY,
UNINTENTIONALLY,

31:41.290 --> 31:43.162
AND WITHOUT MALICE OR
FORETHOUGHT DISAPPEARED DWIGHT,

31:43.205 --> 31:44.946
DID YOU DISAPPEAR HIM
IN A PERMANENT SENSE?

31:44.990 --> 31:46.295
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
THE QUESTION.

31:46.339 --> 31:47.731
DID YOU KILL HIM?
DEAD END!

31:47.775 --> 31:50.125
IS THAT AN ADMISSION?
NO -- DEAD

31:58.046 --> 32:00.962
AAAAHHH!

32:03.138 --> 32:05.010
UH! AH! AAH! NED!

32:05.053 --> 32:07.490
AAAHH! AAH!

32:07.534 --> 32:10.450
THANK GOD FOR MY NATURALLY
CLINGY NATURE.

32:10.493 --> 32:13.018
AAH! NED! NED!

32:13.061 --> 32:14.845
OLIVE, I'M SORRY
I GOT YOU INTO THIS.

32:14.889 --> 32:17.022
I'M SORRY YOU FELT
YOU HAD TO PROVE YOURSELF.

32:17.065 --> 32:19.720
I'M SORRY ABOUT...
SO MANY THINGS.

32:19.763 --> 32:21.852
I'M NOT.
WELL, MAYBE ONE THING.

32:21.896 --> 32:26.205
I'M SORRY YOU NEVER LOOKED AT ME
THE SAME WAY YOU LOOK AT CHUCK.

32:26.248 --> 32:27.771
I WOULDN'T SAY NEVER.

32:27.815 --> 32:29.991
Narrator:
OF ALL THE SECRETS UNTOLD,

32:30.035 --> 32:34.865
THIS WAS THE ONE OLIVE SNOOK
WANTED TO HEAR MOST.

32:34.909 --> 32:40.175
[ BOTH SCREAMING ]

32:40.219 --> 32:41.220
HOLD ON, NED.

32:41.263 --> 32:42.743
HOLD ON.
I GOT YOU.

32:42.786 --> 32:45.485
IF YOU'VE GOT ME,
WHO'S GOT YO-O-O-U?!

32:45.528 --> 32:47.356
Narrator:
THE MYSTERIOUS MASKED MAN

32:47.400 --> 32:49.315
WHO RESCUED
THE PIE MAKER AND OLIVE

32:49.358 --> 32:52.187
WOULD REMAIN
A MYSTERIOUS LOOSE STRING.

32:52.231 --> 32:54.755
REGRETTING
HIS PREVIOUS BAD BEHAVIOR,

32:54.798 --> 32:58.933
EMERSON COD SOUGHT TO TIE UP
ANOTHER LOOSE STRING.

32:58.977 --> 33:01.762
MR. COD, I'M HERE AGAINST
MY BETTER JUDGMENT,

33:01.805 --> 33:03.633
CONSIDERING
THE CALLOUS BRAGGADOCIO

33:03.677 --> 33:07.289
WITH WHICH YOU PREVIOUSLY
GAVE ME THE...HEAVE-HO.

33:07.333 --> 33:09.465
WELL, IF I DID
DO ANY HO-HEAVING,

33:09.509 --> 33:11.032
IT WAS FOR YOUR OWN GOOD.

33:11.076 --> 33:13.600
THERE'S A TIME
FOR CALLOUS BRAGGADOCIO

33:13.643 --> 33:15.254
AND A TIME
FOR SENSITIVITY.

33:15.297 --> 33:17.343
TO THE NORWEGIANS,
THAT TIME IS NEVER.

33:17.386 --> 33:20.433
I SUPPOSE IT'S A HOLDOVER
FROM THEIR VIKING ANCESTRY.

33:20.476 --> 33:22.913
IT WOULD BE DIFFICULT
TO RAPE AND PILLAGE

33:22.957 --> 33:24.654
WITH THE SUBTLETY
OF A HUMANIST.

33:24.698 --> 33:26.700
WELL, THAT'S
WHY I CALLED YOU UP HERE.

33:26.743 --> 33:29.050
I DIDN'T WANT THE VIKINGS
TO GIVE YOU THE NEWS

33:29.094 --> 33:30.617
THAT'LL BREAK YOUR HEART.

33:30.660 --> 33:32.967
THAT SORT OF THING
OUGHT TO COME FROM A FRIEND.

33:33.011 --> 33:34.751
WHEN THE NORWEGIANS
EXHUMED THE BODY

33:34.795 --> 33:38.929
OF YOUR NIECE AND HER FATHER,
THEIR COFFINS WERE EMPTY.

33:38.973 --> 33:42.629
WHAT?
OUR CHARLOTTE?

33:42.672 --> 33:44.413
DWIGHT...STOLE HER?

33:44.457 --> 33:47.112
I WISH THERE WAS SOMETHING
I COULD SAY TO EXPLAIN WHY

33:47.155 --> 33:50.202
OR MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER,
BUT I DO KNOW THIS --

33:50.245 --> 33:55.120
YOU CAN'T STEAL SOMEONE'S SOUL
BY ROBBING THEIR COFFIN.

33:55.163 --> 33:58.862
THE CHARLOTTE THAT YOU KNEW
WASN'T IN THAT BOX.

33:58.906 --> 34:00.647
SHE'S RIGHT HERE
WITH YOU.

34:00.690 --> 34:03.824
AND ALTHOUGH YOU CAN'T SEE HER
OR TALK TO HER ANYMORE,

34:03.867 --> 34:05.086
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE

34:05.130 --> 34:08.872
THAT WHATEVER WAS TAKEN
FROM THAT GRAVE,

34:08.916 --> 34:10.352
THAT WASN'T YOUR NIECE.

34:10.396 --> 34:13.138
THANK YOU...MR. COD.

34:14.487 --> 34:18.360
IT SEEMS
MY SISTER WAS RIGHT.

34:18.404 --> 34:21.537
DWIGHT WAS INDEED
A BAD MAN.

34:21.581 --> 34:23.322
ONLY NOW IT APPEARS

34:23.365 --> 34:28.022
HE WAS MORE OF A MONSTER
THAN SHE OR I EVER KNEW.

34:28.066 --> 34:30.764
OH, MY SWEET,
SWEET CHARLOTTE.

34:30.807 --> 34:34.681
KNOWING THIS WILL SURELY
SHATTER LILY'S HEART.

34:34.724 --> 34:36.596
Narrator:
AS VIVIAN CONTEMPLATED

34:36.639 --> 34:39.164
THE EMOTIONAL DAMAGE
YET TO COME,

34:39.207 --> 34:41.122
IN OLIVE'S APARTMENT,
A GIRL NAMED CHUCK

34:41.166 --> 34:44.430
TENDED TO THE PHYSICAL DAMAGE
ALREADY DONE.

34:44.473 --> 34:45.735
HE KNEW YOUR NAME?

34:45.779 --> 34:48.651
WE THINK OUR MASKED MAN
WAS YOUR POPS.

34:48.695 --> 34:50.175
UH...

34:50.218 --> 34:53.265
I TOLD OLIVE ALL ABOUT YOUR DAD
AND HOW HE...

34:53.308 --> 34:54.483
FAKED HIS OWN DEATH.

34:54.527 --> 34:56.006
OH.

34:56.050 --> 34:57.617
IT MUST HAVE BEEN
YOUR FATHER.

34:57.660 --> 34:59.619
ALTHOUGH, I SAY THAT HAVING
NEVER MET HIM AND NOT

34:59.662 --> 35:01.273
GETTING A GOOD LOOK AT WHO
PULLED US UP FROM THAT CLIFF.

35:01.316 --> 35:03.231
HE WAS COVERED
FROM HEAD TO TOE.

35:03.275 --> 35:06.016
HE HAS A VERY DELICATE
SKIN CONDITION.

35:06.060 --> 35:07.583
LIKE YOUR ALLERGY
TO NED!

35:07.627 --> 35:09.150
YES!
EXACTLY LIKE THAT.

35:09.194 --> 35:10.456
A HEREDITARY LINK.
OHH!

35:10.499 --> 35:13.285
SO OUR MASKED MAN
IS YOUR FATHER.

35:13.328 --> 35:15.200
YES, IT CERTAINLY
SEEMS THAT WAY.

35:15.243 --> 35:19.029
I'M SORRY I THOUGHT YOU WERE
BEING UNREALISTIC BEFORE.

35:19.073 --> 35:21.510
MY REALITY IS THAT DADS
DON'T COME BACK, THEY MOVE ON.

35:21.554 --> 35:23.033
BUT YOUR DAD
DIDN'T MOVE ON, HE --

35:23.077 --> 35:25.906
HOVERED...
LIKE A GUARDIAN ANGEL.

35:25.949 --> 35:29.388
WHAT'S HE GUARDING YOU FROM?

35:29.431 --> 35:31.216
OH, JIMINY JEHOSAPHAT!

35:31.259 --> 35:33.435
I WENT OUT ON A LIMB
FOR YOU PEOPLE --

35:33.479 --> 35:34.958
A TREE LIMB
JUTTING FROM A CLIFF

35:35.002 --> 35:37.178
WITH MY LIMBS DANGLING
OVER CERTAIN DEATH!

35:37.222 --> 35:38.919
SO DON'T LEAVE ME DANGLING

35:38.962 --> 35:42.401
WITH DWIGHT'S DISAPPEARANCE
UNLESS...

35:42.444 --> 35:44.446
HE'S PERMANENTLY
DISAPPEARED,

35:44.490 --> 35:46.970
A.K.A...DEAD,

35:47.014 --> 35:48.189
A.K.A. MURDERED.

35:48.233 --> 35:50.409
OLIVE,
MURDER IS A VERY BIG WORD.

35:50.452 --> 35:51.584
DID HE DIE
OF NATURAL CAUSES?

35:51.627 --> 35:53.238
YES.
YEAH.

35:53.281 --> 35:56.850
ARE EITHER OF YOU REFERRING
TO "MURDER" AS A NATURAL CAUSE?

35:56.893 --> 35:59.766
WE ARE OFFICIALLY
NON-REFERENTIAL STARTING NOW.

35:59.809 --> 36:01.855
WHAT'S STOPPING NOW
ARE THE QUESTIONS.

36:01.898 --> 36:03.552
SO THAT'S HOW IT IS.

36:03.596 --> 36:06.381
YOU WANT TO ROLL ARMY STYLE --
"DON'T ASK, DON'T TELL."

36:06.425 --> 36:10.124
WELL...GUESS WHAT WORKS
IN THE FOX HOLE

36:10.168 --> 36:11.604
WORKS IN THE PIE HOLE.

36:11.647 --> 36:14.128
Narrator:
UNFORTUNATELY FOR OLIVE SNOOK,

36:14.172 --> 36:18.176
WHAT WORKED IN THE PIE HOLE
DID NOT WORK FOR THE NORWEGIANS,

36:18.219 --> 36:22.441
WHO ADHERED TO A STRICT
"DO ASK, DO TELL" POLICY.

36:22.484 --> 36:25.052
I SEE YOU'RE BACK
TO PLAYING FOR THE OTHER TEAM.

36:25.095 --> 36:28.838
HELLO, HEDDA.
YOU'RE LOOKING LOVELY TONIGHT.

36:28.882 --> 36:30.797
YOU KILLED OUR MOTHER!

36:36.803 --> 36:39.719
Olive:
I AM THE VICTIM HERE.

36:39.762 --> 36:41.024
I WAS MOTHER-JACKED.

36:41.068 --> 36:43.201
CAN YOU IDENTIFY
THE PERPETRATORS?

36:43.244 --> 36:45.551
JUST THEIR FISTS
AS THEY PUMMELED MY EYES.

36:45.594 --> 36:47.640
AND THE BOTTOM
OF THEIR BOOTS

36:47.683 --> 36:49.729
AS THEY KICKED ME OUT
OF YOUR MOBILE CRIME LAB...

36:49.772 --> 36:52.862
OUR MOBILE CRIME LAB.
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:52.906 --> 36:54.690
OKAY,
YOUR MOBILE CRIME LAB.

36:54.734 --> 36:57.780
THEN THEY BEAT ME
WITH A BLUE-AND-YELLOW SOCK

36:57.824 --> 37:00.609
AS THEY GOT HIGH ON ABBA
AND TINY LITTLE MEATBALLS.

37:00.653 --> 37:01.871
SWEDES.
SWEDES.

37:01.915 --> 37:03.264
[ Norwegian accent]
THAT'S THEM.

37:03.308 --> 37:08.051
SHOULD I BELIEVE YOU?
YOUR PULSE RACES.

37:08.095 --> 37:10.880
[ Normal voice ]
ONLY BECAUSE
YOU'RE STANDING SO CLOSE.

37:12.230 --> 37:13.492
SHE'S LYING.

37:13.535 --> 37:14.710
WHO ARE YOU PROTECTING?

37:14.754 --> 37:16.059
I'M NOT PROTECTING
ANYBODY.

37:16.103 --> 37:17.844
THAT WOULD IMPLY
THAT I'M PROTECTING

37:17.887 --> 37:19.411
THE PEOPLE
WHO KILLED DWIGHT DIXON.

37:19.454 --> 37:21.282
AND WHY WOULD I PROTECT
KILLERS?

37:21.326 --> 37:23.763
I'M NOT PROTECTING
KILLERS!

37:23.806 --> 37:24.894
[ MELODY PLAYS ]

37:24.938 --> 37:26.853
SHE'S TELLING THE TRUTH.

37:26.896 --> 37:29.421
THERE'S ACTIVITY
ON DIXON'S CREDIT CARD.

37:29.464 --> 37:31.423
HE JUST CHECKED BACK IN
TO THE COME AND SLEEP HOTEL.

37:31.466 --> 37:34.339
YES! HE'S ALIVE!
OUCH.

37:34.382 --> 37:36.297
THAT'S GOOD, HUH?
RIGHT?

37:36.341 --> 37:38.081
YEAH,
THAT'S SOMETHING.

37:38.125 --> 37:41.476
Narrator: RACING TO THE SITE OF
DWIGHT DIXON'S CREDIT-CARD HIT,

37:41.520 --> 37:46.873
THE P.I. AND PIE MAKER
FOUND THEMSELVES IN A JAM.

37:46.916 --> 37:49.441
LISTEN, WE'RE ALL
PROFESSIONALS, PEOPLE.

37:49.484 --> 37:51.225
THIS DOESN'T
HAVE TO GET UGLY.

37:51.269 --> 37:54.184
YOUR SHIRT
SUGGESTS OTHERWISE.

37:54.228 --> 37:56.143
[ GRUNTS ]

37:57.753 --> 38:00.930
ONCE WE FIND DWIGHT,
ALL WILL BE ILLUMINATED.

38:00.974 --> 38:02.845
[ NED GASPS ]

38:02.889 --> 38:04.238
OR NOT.

38:07.285 --> 38:09.896
Nils: WE WILL SOON
GET TO THE BOTTOM OF THIS.

38:09.939 --> 38:12.551
The bottom of this
keeps dropping.

38:12.594 --> 38:14.596
Well, when they get
to the bottom,

38:14.640 --> 38:16.381
what exactly
are they gonna be scraping?

38:16.424 --> 38:18.383
'Cause dead men
don't run up their credit cards

38:18.426 --> 38:20.689
checking back into motels
they never checked out of.

38:20.733 --> 38:23.170
You don't think Chuck's dad
could have done all this?

38:23.213 --> 38:26.260
WHATEVER RIDICULOUS SPECULATIONS
YOU HAVE ARE MOOT.

38:26.304 --> 38:28.349
THE DETAILS
SPEAK LOUD AND CLEAR.

38:28.393 --> 38:31.004
COME, DETAILS.
SPEAK TO US.

38:31.047 --> 38:34.442
Narrator: THE DETAILS IN THE
CASE DID SPEAK LOUD AND CLEAR.

38:34.486 --> 38:37.053
BUT THE STORY THEY TOLD
WAS A LIE,

38:37.097 --> 38:38.794
FOR THE FACTS WERE
NOT THESE --

38:38.838 --> 38:41.623
EVERY ITEM
SCRUTINIZED IN THE ROOM

38:41.667 --> 38:43.669
TOLD A STORY PRECISELY CRAFTED.

38:43.712 --> 38:46.541
FOR, DESPITE THE FACT
THAT DWIGHT DIXON'S LIFE

38:46.585 --> 38:49.109
HAD SIMPLY GOTTEN UP
AND LEFT HIM,

38:49.152 --> 38:51.024
THE LACK
OF VISIBLE SIGNS OF TRAUMA

38:51.067 --> 38:53.374
TOLD A FAR MORE LOGICAL TALE

38:53.418 --> 38:57.117
OF A MAN WHO HAD SIMPLY DIED
OF NATURAL CAUSES.

38:57.160 --> 39:00.990
THE HIDDEN BOOTY
OF HEIRLOOMS AND GOLD CROWNS

39:01.034 --> 39:02.383
STASHED UNDER THE MATTRESS

39:02.427 --> 39:04.167
IMPLIED
A SEASONED GRAVE ROBBER

39:04.211 --> 39:05.691
AND THE CAN OF FUEL ACCELERANT

39:05.734 --> 39:10.652
INDICATED THE TWO BODIES ROBBED
HAD GONE UP IN FLAMES.

39:10.696 --> 39:12.524
IN THE END,
ALL THE EVIDENCE POINTED

39:12.567 --> 39:15.483
TO DWIGHT ACTING
AND DYING ALONE,

39:15.527 --> 39:17.398
HEH!
WITH NOBODY ELSE
RESPONSIBLE

39:17.442 --> 39:21.794
HEH.
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT
THEY WERE SUPPOSED TO FIND.

39:26.059 --> 39:27.582
[ BOTH SIGH ]

39:32.152 --> 39:34.720
Narrator:
AND VIVIAN CHARLES FOUND HERSELF

39:34.763 --> 39:36.939
BUOYING
HER SISTER LILY'S SPIRITS

39:36.983 --> 39:38.419
AFTER LEARNING

39:38.463 --> 39:41.379
THAT THEIR BELOVED
CHARLOTTE'S BODY WAS GONE.

39:42.989 --> 39:45.600
MEANWHILE,
THE PIE MAKER MEDITATED

39:45.644 --> 39:47.602
ON HIS OWN RESPONSIBILITIES.

39:47.646 --> 39:48.864
ANY SIGN OF YOUR DAD?

39:48.908 --> 39:49.909
NOPE.

39:49.952 --> 39:52.041
NO HIDE NOR HAIR
NOR BUTTON.

39:52.085 --> 39:53.869
BUT HE'S OUT THERE
SOMEWHERE.

39:53.913 --> 39:55.349
I DON'T KNOW
IF I LIKE THE IDEA

39:55.393 --> 39:57.177
OF CHARLES CHARLES
AS MY GUARDIAN ANGEL.

39:57.220 --> 39:59.571
HE HASN'T TOLD ANYONE
THAT THERE'S A PIE MAKER

39:59.614 --> 40:05.490
WHO HAS A KNACK FOR BAKING
AND WAKING THE DEAD.

40:05.533 --> 40:07.970
YOU'RE --
YOU'RE USING FRESH FRUIT.

40:08.014 --> 40:11.191
I AM NOW --
I MEAN FROM NOW ON.

40:11.234 --> 40:13.454
TOUCHING DEAD THINGS
HAS ONLY GOTTEN ME INTO TROUBLE,

40:13.498 --> 40:15.630
SO...NO MORE.

40:15.674 --> 40:16.979
BESIDES, I'VE ALREADY GOT

40:17.023 --> 40:20.113
THE BEST THING
I'M GONNA GET FROM IT.

40:20.156 --> 40:21.941
YOU.

40:21.984 --> 40:23.943
NO MORE DEAD FRUIT,
NO MORE DEAD PEOPLE?

40:23.986 --> 40:26.336
YEAH,
I'M GOING COLD TURKEY.

40:26.380 --> 40:29.470
FROM NOW ON, INVESTIGATING CRIME
IS EMERSON'S BUSINESS,

40:29.514 --> 40:32.604
AND BAKING PIE IS MINE.

40:32.647 --> 40:34.083
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.

40:34.127 --> 40:35.650
I'M NOT LOOKING
TO BLAME ANYONE.

40:35.694 --> 40:38.131
WAKING THE DEAD CREATES
TOO MANY UNFORTUNATE VARIABLES,

40:38.174 --> 40:40.655
AND I'M JUST TAKING MYSELF
OUT OF THE EQUATION.

40:40.699 --> 40:42.744
BUT MY DAD --
HE ALREADY FIXED EVERYTHING.

40:42.788 --> 40:44.790
I DON'T WANT YOUR DAD
OR ANYONE ELSE'S

40:44.833 --> 40:48.533
TO FIGHT MY BATTLES
OR CLEAN UP MY MESSES.

40:48.576 --> 40:50.622
SO THAT'S IT?

40:50.665 --> 40:52.580
THAT'S IT.

40:52.624 --> 40:56.192
Narrator:
WHILE THE PIE MAKER TOOK
RESPONSIBILITY FOR HIS ACTIONS,

40:56.236 --> 41:00.196
HE WAS WRONG ABOUT THE DAD
WHO FOUGHT HIS BATTLES.

41:00.240 --> 41:03.461
IT WASN'T CHUCK'S FATHER
WHO CLEANED UP

41:03.504 --> 41:07.508
THIS PARTICULAR MESS.

41:07.552 --> 41:10.293
IT WAS THE PIE MAKER'S FATHER.
